nly covers the backend application and doesn't include frontend ID token acquisition methods. This is important context for users to understand what the sample actually demonstrates.\n\nMoving to the structure section, I'm verifying that all the classes and interfaces are properly captured - the interfaces like IdTokenVerifier and SignatureAlgorithmProvider, along with the implementation classes for Cognito integration and the business action classes are all accounted for in the knowledge file. The class diagram itself is just an image reference without text content, but the detailed class descriptions and their responsibilities are all there.\n\nNow I'm cross-checking the descriptions against the source material - the wording for CognitoIdTokenVerifier and CognitoSignatureAlgorithmProvider descriptions are slightly paraphrased in the knowledge file but convey the same meaning, so these aren't fabrications, just natural compression of the original text.\n\nFor the V3 section count issue, the automated warning about 7 headings was counting all heading levels, but the actual h2 count in the source is 3, which matches the knowledge file sections, so there's no problem there.\n\nI'm noticing the source text about \"本サンプルで取り扱う範囲\" appears to be cut off mid-sentence, so I need to see what comes next to understand what's being omitted. この部分は確かに知識ファイルs2に明示的には含まれていないようだ。s2ではIDトークンがフロントエンドで取得されることは触れられているが、本サンプルがバックエンド処理のみを対象としていて、フロントエンドのIDトークン取得方法は対象外という明確な境界線が記載されていない。ユーザーが「このサンプルはフロントエンド部分も含まれているか」と質問した場合、この情報があると正確に対象外であることを伝えられる。\n\nV4ヒントの確認では、s1とs2の両方で必要なキーワードが揃っているようだが、スコープの明示的な制限についてはマイナーな欠落として記録しておく必要がある。\n\ns3のクラス名も全て確認できた。Cognitoパッケージの説明では、両パッケージの考え方が同じであることが述べられているようだが、ページ全体ではCognitoパッケージに焦点を当てているようだ。\n\nつまり、adb2cパッケージを使う場合は、対応するコンポーネントに読み替える必要があるという重要な注記が知識ファイルに含まれていない。これはドキュメントがCognito中心であることと、adb2cユーザーがどう対応すべきかを示す実装上の重要な情報だ。 The cognito-as-base note is actually more important than I initially thought—without it, adb2c users might not realize they need to swap out components, which could lead to confusion even if it doesn't break implementation. Both omissions are minor since the packages are listed and the backend focus is clear, but they're more about helpful context than critical gaps. Let me verify there are no fabrications by checking against the original document. I'm reconsidering whether the second omission about component substitution for adb2c users should be classified as minor or more critical—if someone asks how to use the adb2c package, the AI needs to know the docs are cognito-based and require component swaps, otherwise guidance could be confusing. But since neither omission causes actual implementation failures, I'll keep both marked as minor with important contextual notes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14253,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":14253,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"76e06646-1341-40f7-9017-f69d49061d44","uuid":"1188e6be-a8f3-4102-bbe9-281f78afbac6"}
